# Connect display screen is frozen

The **Public TV pairing / “Connect display” landing** (`Quizz'em TV` + 4-letter join code) is **approved as-is**. Do **not** modify it unless the user **explicitly countermands** this rule (e.g. “change the connect display screen”, “resize pairing typography”, “update PairingScreen”).

## Protected files and tokens

- `apps/display/src/PairingScreen.tsx`
- `apps/display/src/DisplayGate.tsx` — only when the change affects pairing/bootstrap UI
- Pairing typography in `apps/display/src/index.css`:
  - `.display-text-pairing-label`
  - `.display-text-pairing-title`
  - `.display-text-pairing-body`
  - `.display-text-pairing-code`
- Pairing exports in `apps/display/src/displayTypography.ts`:
  - `DISPLAY_TEXT_PAIRING_*`

## Do not change (without explicit user request)

- Copy, layout, spacing, card width, colors, or typography scale on the pairing screen
- Refactors that move pairing styles into shared tokens and alter how the screen looks
- “Drive-by” fixes, responsive tweaks, or viewport-rule cleanups that touch pairing

## Allowed without countermand

- Bug fixes that **only** fix crashes, broken socket pairing, or incorrect join-code **logic** — **only if** visual/copy/layout stay identical; mention the exception in the commit message
- Renames/moves that preserve **pixel-identical** output (rare; prefer leaving files alone)

## When the user countermands

Proceed with their specific pairing/connect-display instructions only for that turn (or scope they name). Do not broaden changes beyond what they asked.

## Checklist before merging any display change

- [ ] Did this diff touch protected pairing files or CSS/tokens above? If yes, did the user explicitly request it?
- [ ] If pairing was touched without user request, revert those hunks.
